      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): surface multi-account default routing warnings in preview and lint",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nFixes an issue where `openclaw doctor` preview and `openclaw doctor --lint` did not surface warnings about multi-account channels that lack explicit default routing or complete account-scoped bindings.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nSurface `collectMissingDefaultAccountBindingWarnings` and `collectMissingExplicitDefaultAccountWarnings` through `collectDoctorPreviewNotes` so both preview and lint paths show routing warnings. Removed the duplicate direct calls from `doctor-config-flow` to avoid double-emission — the preview/lint path surfaces them via the health check contribution, and the repair path via the ordered doctor checks.\n\n## User Impact\nOperators running `openclaw doctor` preview or `openclaw doctor --lint` now see warnings when multi-account channels lack explicit default routing, without duplicate output in the full doctor flow.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Tests:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor/shared/preview-warnings.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  64 passed (64)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  44 passed (44)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/flows/doctor-core-checks.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  55 passed (55)\n```",
        "branch": "fix/doctor-preview-default-account-warnings",
